span%3E.%20I%20didn't%20burn%20any%20bridges%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20sour%20taste%20left%20in%20both%20our%20mouths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHeed%20my%20advice%3A%20Just%20be%20honest.%20If%20it's%20time%20to%20go%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20go.%20I%20know%20it's%20hard%20sometimes%20to%20open%20up%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-manager-tough-time-big-tech-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehigher%20management%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eabout%20personal%20matters%2C%20but%20the%20alternative%20is%20worse.%20Trust%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-properly-quit-your-job-employee-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727093550000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f150b9cfb7f307e573d009%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-properly-quit-your-job-employee-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Before%20quitting%20my%20corporate%20job%2C%20I%20called%20out%20sick%20for%20a%20week%20and%20villanized%20my%20boss.%20I%20regret%20not%20handling%20the%20situation%20more%20professionally.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Georgie%20Tzintzis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-properly-quit-your-job-employee-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20EY%20Saga%2C%20And%20The%20Tyranny%20Of%20Work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F6q2gv398_ey_625x300_23_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20true%20that%20hard%20work%20never%20killed%20anybody%2C%20but%20I%20figure%20why%20take%20the%20chance.%26quot%3B%20The%20origin%20of%20this%20cheeky%20quote%2C%20often%20found%20on%20teenagers'%20T-shirts%2C%20is%20at%20a%20Washington%20dinner%20in%201987.%20The%20self-deprecating%20quip%20came%20mid-speech%20from%20then-US%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20who%20was%20often%20targeted%20for%20being%20%26quot%3Blazy%20and%20lethargic%26quot%3B%20and%20loving%20his%20afternoon%20naps.%20It%20is%20not%20ageing%20well%20in%20a%20world%20where%20the%20toxic%20productivity%20treadmill%20is%20gathering%20speed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnending%20work%20hours%2C%20the%20current%20default%20for%20hard%20work%2C%20are%20indeed%20killing%20people.%20Very%20young%20people.%20A%2026-year-old%20chartered%20accountant%20employed%20with%20EY%20in%20Pune%20reportedly%20died%20from%20her%20workload%20earlier%20this%20week.%20Anna%20Augustine%20was%20just%20four%20months%20into%20her%20first%20job%20at%20the%20audit%20and%20consulting%20firm%2C%20one%20of%20the%20global%20Big%20Four.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'She%20Kept%20Pushing%20Herself'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20worked%20tirelessly%20at%20EY%2C%20giving%20her%20all%20to%20meet%20the%20demands%20placed%20on%20her.%20However%2C%20the%20workload%2C%20new%20environment%2C%20and%20long%20hours%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20her%20physically%2C%20emotionally%2C%20and%20mentally.%20She%20began%20experiencing%20anxiety%2C%20sleeplessness%2C%20and%20stress%20soon%20after%20joining%2C%20but%20she%20kept%20pushing%20herself%2C%20believing%20that%20hard%20work%20and%20perseverance%20were%20the%20keys%20to%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Anna's%20grieving%20mother%20Anita%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20EY%20chief%20Rajiv%20Memani.%20She%20wrote%20how%20Anna's%20managers%20dumped%20work%20on%20her%20at%20odd%20hours%20because%20they%20wanted%20to%20watch%20cricket%20matches.%20When%20she%20raised%20concerns%20about%20being%20unable%20to%20rest%2C%20she%20was%20told%20working%20nights%20was%20normal%20and%20that%20is%20what%20she%20should%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20rat%20race%20has%20ensured%20that%20working%20long%20hours%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20badge%20of%20honour.%20It%20is%20often%20normalised%20by%20leaders%20people%20look%20up%20to.%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20takes%20pride%20in%20barely%20sleeping%20because%20he%20works%20almost%20round%20the%20clock.%20Although%20the%20PM%20allows%20that%20such%20punishing%20workaholism%20is%20not%20for%20everyone%2C%20it%20inspires%20many%20to%20egg%20others%20on%20with%20his%20example%20at%20the%20peril%20of%20their%20health.%20Business%20tycoon%20Narayana%20Murthy%20believes%20young%20people%20should%20raise%20productivity%20and%20work%20harder%2C%20at%20least%2070%20hours%20a%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20here%20is%20not%20against%20hard%2C%20productive%20work.%20It%20is%20a%20cavill%20against%20the%20yardstick%2C%20which%20routinely%20is%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20and%20not%20the%20content%20of%20the%20job%20done.%20Never%20in%20human%20history%20have%20young%20white-collar%20workers%20toiled%20so%20relentlessly%20in%20service%20of%20corporate%20goals%20(read%20profits).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Inescapable%20White-Collar%20Grind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESlave-driving%20employees%20was%20a%20managerial%20trait%20confined%20once%20upon%20a%20time%20to%20sweatshops%20and%20informal%20shop%20floors.%20But%20now%20white-collar%20grind%20is%20particularly%20overdone%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20finance%20and%20consulting%20sectors.%20Others%20such%20as%20law%20firms%20and%20even%20some%20non-profit%20foundations%20aren't%20far%20behind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutrage%20engulfed%20Wall%20Street%20in%20May%20when%20a%2035-year-old%20Bank%20of%20America%20associate%20died%20after%20logging%20multiple%20100-hour%20weeks.%20The%20banking%20industry%20already%20had%20work-hour%20restrictions%2C%20which%20were%20put%20in%20place%20a%20decade%20ago%20after%20a%20sleep-deprived%20intern%20died%20of%20a%20seizure.%20A%20%3Cem%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20%3C%2Fem%3Einvestigation%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3Blong%20hours%20and%20deference%20to%20bosses'%20commands%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20unreasonable%2C%20are%20the%20norm%20industrywide%26quot%3B.%20Novice%20workers%20were%20always%20at%20the%20receiving%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverwork%20and%20burnout%20risk%20have%20spread%20to%20unexpected%20fields.%20Elite%20footballers%20in%20Europe%20are%20contemplating%20a%20strike%20after%20more%20matches%20were%20added%20to%20their%20annual%20schedule.%20The%20warning%20came%20from%20Manchester%20City%20midfielder%20Rodri%2C%20who%20is%20expected%20to%20play%20as%20many%20as%2075%20games%20for%20club%20and%20country%20in%20the%202024-25%20season.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20too%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodri%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BNot%20everything%20is%20about%20money%20or%20marketing.%20It%20is%20about%20the%20quality%20on%20show.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackbreaking%20Work%2C%20Everywhere%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClub%20owners%2C%20regulators%20and%20broadcasters%20are%20naturally%20happy%20to%20add%20matches%20in%20pursuit%20of%20revenues%20and%20profits.%20That%20even%20superstar%20sportspersons%20feel%20the%20heat%20of%20organised%20greed%20says%20something.%20Financiers%20would%20see%20it%20as%20elevating%20productivity%20and%20sweating%20assets.%20But%20as%20Rodri%20quipped%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20am%20not%20tired%20I%20perform%20better.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack-breaking%20work%20in%20other%20areas%20that%20was%20hardly%20visible%20in%20public%20discourse%20is%20now%20in%20focus.%20Rising%20demand%20for%20maternity%20leave%20and%20benefits%20has%20put%20the%20spotlight%20on%20unpaid%20household%20work%20done%20by%20pregnant%20women%2C%20especially%20in%20tradition-bound%20villages.%20The%20setting%20may%20be%20different%2C%20but%20the%20work%20afflicted%20on%20household%20novices%20(read%20young%20brides)%20is%20similar%20to%20what%20Anna%20went%20through%20at%20EY.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGreed%20At%20All%20Levels%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20end%20to%20greed%20and%20it%20is%20stacked%20up%20from%20the%20supervisors%20at%20the%20lowest%20level%2C%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20extract%20the%20most%20from%20their%20workers%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20the%20fat%20return-seekers%20who%20put%20up%20the%20dough.%20As%20Arun%20Maira%2C%20former%20chairman%20of%20BCG%2C%20argues%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20social%20and%20business%20culture%20of%20greed%20for%20more%20wealth%2C%20in%20which%20they%20are%20all%20locked%2C%20will%20not%20be%20easy%20to%20change.%20But%20it%20must%20be%20changed%20to%20make%20the%20world%20better%20for%20everyone%26quot%3B.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20wishful%20thinking.%20The%20pandemic-inspired%20introspection%20and%20debate%20around%20work%2C%20supervision%2C%20management%2C%20automation%2C%20lay-offs%20and%20living%20has%20fizzled%20out.%20Amazon%2C%20which%20cut%2027%2C000%20jobs%20in%202023%2C%20reverting%20to%20a%20five-day%20work-week%20perhaps%20is%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20pandemic-induced%20corporate%20forbearance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20will%20only%20increase%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20proliferates%20in%20the%20workplace.%20Human%20beings%2C%20whose%20productivity%20and%20quality%20of%20work%20depend%20on%20their%20physical%20and%20psychological%20state%2C%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20match%20always%20-%20on%20AI's%20evenness%20and%20steady%20state.%20For%20companies%2C%20it%20eliminates%20the%20need%20to%20spend%20on%20maintaining%20the%20physical%20and%20psychological%20health%20of%20their%20workers.%20It's%20cost-effective%2C%20productive%2C%20and%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20anti-human.%20So%20are%20certain%20managerial%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Dinesh%20Narayanan%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20journalist%20and%20author%20of%20'The%20RSS%20And%20The%20Making%20Of%20The%20Deep%20Nation'.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727093520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F0bhcghpo_ey_625x300_23_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fey-saga-and-the-tyranny-of-work-6630996%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20no%20end%20to%20greed%20and%20it%20is%20stacked%20up%20from%20the%20supervisors%20at%20the%20lowest%20level%2C%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20extract%20the%20most%20from%20their%20workers%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20the%20fat%20return-seekers%20who%20put%20up%20the%20dough.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fey-saga-and-the-tyranny-of-work-6630996%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22100%20Killed%2C%20Over%20400%20Injured%20In%20Israeli%20Strikes%2C%20Says%20Lebanon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELebanon's%20health%20ministry%20said%20Israeli%20strikes%20on%20the%20south%20killed%20100%20people%20and%20wounded%20more%20than%20400%20others%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20worst%20toll%20in%20nearly%20a%20year%20of%20cross-border%20clashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEnemy%20raids%20on%20southern%20towns%20and%20villages%20since%20this%20morning...%20killed%20100%20and%20injured%20more%20than%20400%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20health%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20updating%20earlier%20figures%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bchildren%2C%20women%20and%20paramedics%26quot%3B%20were%20among%20the%20casualties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20t