022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bat-will%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20meaning%20an%20employer%20can%20terminate%20them%20at%20any%20time%20as%20long%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20dismissal%20is%20not%20illegal.%20At-will%20employment%20also%20means%20that%20an%20employee%20can%20quit%20at%20any%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnless%20you%20can%20assert%20some%20type%20of%20statutory%20rights%2C%20an%20employer%20can%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20forcing%20employees%20back%20into%20the%20office%20full-time%2C%20said%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDomenique%20Camacho%20Moran%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Farrell%20Fritz%20in%20New%20York%2C%20who%20tends%20to%20represent%20management%20in%20employment-related%20matters%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20most%20employees%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20have%20a%20choice%26quot%3B%20regarding%20how%20their%20job%20is%20performed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbsent%20some%20contractual%20obligation%2C%20it%20is%20the%20employer's%20decision%20as%20to%20whether%20a%20job%20should%20or%20should%20not%20be%20performed%20remotely%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20Moran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20an%20employee%20was%20specifically%20hired%20as%20a%20remote%20worker%2C%20unless%20a%20written%20contract%20guarantees%20remote%20work%20for%20a%20set%20period%20of%20time%2C%20that%20employee%20still%20would%20have%20no%20legal%20grounds%20to%20push%20back%20against%20an%20RTO%20policy%2C%20the%20attorneys%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20law%20in%20any%20state%2C%20there's%20no%20law%20on%20the%20federal%20level%2C%20that%20gives%20anyone%20the%20right%20to%20just%20say%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20and%20that's%20my%20right.'%20So%20until%20that%20changes%2C%20you%20have%20to%20fit%20into%20something%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20an%20employee%20using%20a%20medical%20reason%20to%20justify%20working%20from%20home%20would%20have%20t