alUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Even%20millennials%20are%20getting%20too%20old%20to%20land%20a%20tech%20job%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20baby%20staring%20at%20a%20laptop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66edc92ed17aa3c7b2b4b75f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EThomasVogel%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20in%20tech%2C%20your%20suspicions%20were%20right%3A%20Gen%20Z%20is%20starting%20to%20eat%20your%20lunch.%20Newly%20released%20federal%20data%20shows%20the%20US%20tech%20workforce%20is%20younger%20than%20the%20workforce%20at%20large%20and%20getting%20younger%20still.%20Tech%20workers%20under%2025%20are%20becoming%20more%20common%2C%20while%20the%20proportion%20of%20workers%20older%20than%2040%20shrinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20age-old%20perception%20that%20tech%20workers%20should%20be%20young%20so%20they%20can%20move%20fast%20and%20break%20things.%20Job%20applicants%20are%20assessed%20on%20whether%20they're%20a%20%26quot%3Bculture%20fit%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20culture%20often%20toasts%20youth.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20stress%20the%20importance%20of%20being%20young%20and%20technical.%20Young%20people%20are%20just%20smarter%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20then-22-year-old%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20(he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-birthday-party-tshirt-chain-priscilla-chan-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eturned%2040%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year).%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20actually%20showing%20ageism%2C%20the%20problem%20has%20been%20there's%20more%20bad%20vibes%20than%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20report%20from%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%20released%20this%20month%20puts%20some%20numbers%20to%20those%20vibes.%20The%20commission%20looked%20at%20more%20than%2010%20million%20workers%20employed%20in%20the%20tech%20workforce%20(which%20included%20workers%20across%20industries%20employed%20in%2056%20STEM-related%20roles)%20as%20of%202022%20and%20found%20that%20nearly%2041%25%20were%20ages%2025%20to%2039%2C%20an%20age%20group%20that%20made%20up%20just%2033%25%20of%20the%20overall%20US%20workforce.%20Even%20younger%20workers%20were%20faring%20better%20in%20tech%3A%20The%20number%20of%20people%20under%20the%20age%20of%2025%20grew%20by%20about%209%25%20each%20year%20from%202014%20to%202022%20and%20made%20up%207%25%20of%20the%20tech%20workforce%20by%202022%2C%20more%20than%2020%20times%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20for%20young%20workers%20across%20all%20industries.%20One%20of%20the%20top%20qualifications%20to%20land%20a%20tech%20job%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20is%20to%20possess%20a%20birth%20certificate%20dated%20after%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ranks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-corporate-gerontocracy-aging-ceos-retirement-succession-replacement-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkers%20over%2065%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20also%20grow%2C%20but%20only%20to%204%25%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20still%20by%20far%20the%20smallest%20age%20group%20working%20in%20tech%2C%20and%20far%20less%20represented%20compared%20with%20their%20ranks%20in%20other%20industries.%20The%20EEOC's%20report%2C%20which%20for%20the%20first%20time%20looked%20at%20age%20discrimination%2C%20included%20an%20even%20more%20troubling%20finding%3A%20Charges%20of%20age%20discrimination%20are%20more%20prevalent%20among%20companies%20where%20STEM%20jobs%20are%20prominent.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshocked-when-recruiter-said-too-old-tech-job-ageism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAge%20complaints%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20found%20in%20nearly%2020%25%20of%20the%20charges%20filed%20to%20the%20EEOC%20at%20these%20companies%2C%20compared%20with%2015%25%20across%20other%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20none%20of%20it%20is%20good%20news%2C%20for%20many%2C%20it%20is%20validation.%20The%20report%20%26quot%3Bfinally%20brought%20to%20life%20that%20this%20is%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Maureen%20Clough%2C%20who%20hosts%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BIt%20Gets%20Late%20Early%26quot%3B%20about%20aging%20in%20the%20tech%20world.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20gaslit%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20age%20isn't%20the%20tech%20world's%20only%20workforce%20problem.%20The%20EEOC%20also%20found%20that%20women%20and%20Black%20workers%20continue%20to%20be%20disproportionately%20underrepresented%2C%20and%20that%20discrimination%20in%20the%20industry%20is%20likely%20a%20contributor%20to%20age%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20racial%20disparities%20in%20the%20tech%20sector.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-men-as-a-female-software-engineer-is-difficult-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20up%20just%2022%25%20of%20tech%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20proportion%20of%20jobs%20they%20held%20in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAge%20is%20often%20bumped%20to%20a%20secondary%20consideration%20behind%20other%20demographics%20in%20the%20push%20for%20diversity.%20That%20may%20be%20because%20many%20people%20don't%20really%20think%20ageism%20is%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20US%20law%20has%20prohibited%20discrimination%20against%20workers%20over%20the%20age%20of%2040%20since%201967.%20Stereotypes%20and%20complaints%20about%20both%20the%20young%20and%20old%20remain%20embedded%20in%20society%2C%20and%20are%20questioned%20less%20than%20preconceived%20notions%20about%20race%2C%20sexuality%2C%20and%20gender.%20Certain%20behaviors%2C%20whether%20attempting%20to%20delay%20aging%20with%20antiaging%20serums%20or%20outright%20mocking%20older%20people%20with%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20boomer%26quot%3B%20memes%2C%20have%20been%20seen%20largely%20as%20privileges%20of%20the%20young%20rather%20than%20antagonistic.%20Ageism%20is%20associated%20with%20worsened%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20social%20isolation%2C%20loneliness%2C%20financial%20insecurity%2C%20and%20even%20early%20death.%20Forty%20is%20the%20age%20typically%20pinpointed%20as%20older%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20but%20in%20China%2C%20the%20threat%20looms%2C%20too%2C%20and%20workers%20speak%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcurse%20of%2035%2C%26quot%3B%20fearful%20that%20even%20reaching%20that%20age%20could%20lead%20to%20diminished%20career%20opportunities%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20new%20data%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20we%20don't%20know.%20Joanna%20Lahey%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20University%20who%20studies%20age%20discrimination%2C%20says%20the%20report%20shows%20a%20correlation%20between%20youth%20and%20tech%20employment%2C%20but%20the%20exact%20cause%20is%20unclear.%20A%20lagging%20representation%20of%20older%20workers%20could%20come%20from%20discrimination%20in%20hiring%2C%20training%2C%20or%20retention.%20But%20it%20could%20also%20show%20that%20older%20workers%20are%20retiring%20while%20more%20young%20people%20are%20entering%20the%20workforce.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20the%20true%20extent%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20and%20importantly%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20we%20do%20not%20know%20how%20to%20fix%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Lahey%20wrote%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-tech-job-hunt-given-up-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20only%20heightened%20suspicions%20of%20ageism.%20More%20than%20130%2C000%20tech%20workers%20have%20been%20laid%20off%20worldwide%20this%20year%2C%20continuing%20a%20trend%20that%20began%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20Layoffs.fyi%2C%20a%20site%20that%20tracks%20job%20cuts%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20John%20Zeman%2C%20a%20former%20employee%20of%20X%2C%20then%20Twitter%2C%20is%20suing%20the%20company%20after%20he%20was%20laid%20off%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-elon-musk-supports-donald-trump-election-save-tesla-disaster-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%2051%2C%20took%20over%20in%20November%202022%20and%20gutted%20the%20staff.%20Zeman%20was%2063%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20his%20suit%20claims%20that%2060%25%20of%20workers%20at%20Twitter%20older%20than%2050%20were%20cut%20in%20the%20layoffs%2C%20compared%20with%2054%25%20of%20workers%20under%20the%20age%20of%2050.%20In%20early%20September%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20ruled%20the%20class-action%20lawsuit%20could%20move%20forward%2C%20finding%20that%20the%20allegations%20rose%20beyond%20%26quot%3Bmere%20speculation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%20and%20X%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20But%20these%20cases%20can%20be%20tricky%3B%20if%20the%20older%20workers%20were%20higher%20paid%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20cuts%20might%20be%20defended%20with%20cost-saving%20reasons.%20Former%20workers%20at%20IBM%20had%20also%20sued%20the%20company%2C%20alleging%20people%20over%2040%20were%20laid%20off%20at%20higher%20rates%20than%20younger%20workers%2C%20but%20IBM%20has%20been%20able%20to%20block%20some%20of%20those%20claims%20(the%20company%20has%20denied%20engaging%20in%20%26quot%3Bsystemic%20age%20discrimination%26quot%3B).%20Cases%20like%20these%20are%20massive%20gambles%3A%20They%20could%20be%20major%20wins%20for%20holding%20tech%20companies%20accountable%20for%20ageist%20practices%2C%20or%20create%20a%20chilling%20effect%20that%20stops%20others%20from%20fighting%20in%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20ageism%20is%20overt%2C%20and%20other%20times%20it%20just%20leaves%20workers%20with%20an%20inkling.%20John%20Rizzo%2C%20a%2060-year-old%2C%20says%20he%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20two%20years%20applying%20for%20jobs%20in%20product%20management%2C%20but%20he%20feels%20his%20age%20is%20the%20reason%20he's%20still%20unemployed.%20Rizzo%20says%20he%20has%20450%20versions%20of%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20has%20applied%20to%20more%20than%204%2C000%20jobs.%20He%20does%20well%20on%20phone%20screens%20but%20says%20a%20recruiter's%20tone%20then%20seems%20to%20change%20once%20they%20get%20on%20a%20Zoom%20call%20and%20see%20his%20age.%20It's%20a%20hurdle%20to%20finding%20a%20tech%20job%20that%20he%20didn't%20have%20in%20the%20past.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20heartbreaking%2C%26quot%3B%20Rizzo%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20me.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20doing%20something%20wrong.%26quot%3B%20He's%20done%20some%20work%20for%20a%20startup%20he%20cofounded%20and%20as%20a%20contractor%20for%20other%20companies%2C%20but%20he%20says%20he%20is%20also%20making%20ends%20meet%20by%20working%20as%20a%20security%20guard.%20Rizzo%20says%20the%20absence%20of%20experienced%20workers%20like%20him%20is%20a%20loss%20for%20tech%20companies.%20%26quot%3BGen%20X%20built%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20ton%20of%20value%20there.%20There's%20a%20ton%20of%20experience%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20for%20an%20intergenerational%20workforce%20isn't%20just%20moral%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20practical.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lse.ac.uk%2Ftii%2Fassets%2Fdocuments%2Flse-generations-survey-report-global.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20The%20Inclusion%20Initiative%20at%20The%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20examining%20roughly%201%2C500%20UK%20and%20US%20workers%20in%20tech%2C%20finance%2C%20and%20professional%20services%20found%20that%20employees%20at%20companies%20with%20age-inclusive%20work%20practices%20were%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20be%20satisfied%20with%20their%20job%20and%20less%20than%20half%20as%20likely%20to%20look%20for%20new%20roles.%20These%20workers%20also%20reported%20feeling%20low%20levels%20of%20productivity%20less%20frequently.%20Combining%20workers%20from%20generations%20brings%20together%20people%20with%20different%20knowledge%2C%20perspective%2C%20and%20social%20networks%2C%20said%20Daniel%20Jolles%2C%20a%20behavioral-science%20researcher%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20have%20good%20diversity%2C%20we%20can%20get%20more%20productive%20outcomes%20under%20the%20right%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Jolles%20said.%20And%20that%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20argument%20that%20might%20catch%20the%20eye%20of%20business%20leaders.%20After%20all%2C%20they're%20not%20getting%20any%20younger%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-ageism-tech-jobs-gen-z-boomers-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727085302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66edc949ce3009a0fac83317%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-ageism-tech-jobs-gen-z-boomers-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It's%20official%3A%20The%20ranks%20of%20tech%20workers%20under%2025%20are%20rising%2C%20while%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20over%2040%20is%20shrinking.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-ageism-tech-jobs-gen-z-boomers-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%