20drew%20him%20to%20activism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Mr%20Dissanayake's%20cousin%20was%20killed%20during%20the%20government's%20crackdown%20on%20the%20JVP's%20second%20insurrection%20in%201988.%20This%20period%20also%20saw%20his%20family%20home%20destroyed%2C%20deepening%20his%20resolve%20to%20remain%20loyal%20to%20the%20JVP's%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20evolution%20and%20leadership%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20JVP%20maintained%20a%20staunch%20anti-imperialist%20and%20socialist%20position%2C%20but%20by%20the%201980s%2C%20it%20shifted%20towards%20Sinhala%20nationalism.%20The%20party%20fiercely%20opposed%20Tamil%20political%20claims%20and%20external%20intervention%20in%20Sri%20Lanka's%20ethnic%20conflict.%20After%20being%20banned%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20later%20legalised%2C%20the%20JVP%20entered%20mainstream%20politics%2C%20winning%20seats%20in%20parliament.%20Mr%20Dissanayake%20himself%20became%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20in%202000%20and%20briefly%20served%20as%20the%20Minister%20of%20Agriculture%20under%20President%20Chandrika%20Kumaratunga%20Bandaranaike%20between%202004%20and%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fjkv96n4o_anura-kumara-dissanayaka-afp_625x300_23_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20leader%20of%20the%20JVP%2C%20succeeding%20Somawansa%20Amarasinghe.%20Under%20his%20leadership%2C%20the%20party%20underwent%20significant%20changes%2C%20focusing%20on%20expanding%20its%20political%20base.%20Recognising%20that%20the%20JVP's%20traditional%20appeal%20was%20limited%2C%20Mr%20Dissanayeke%20formed%20the%20National%20People's%20Power%20(NPP)%20Alliance%2C%20bringing%20together%20over%20two%20dozen%20political%20groups%2C%20professionals%2C